# Resource Integrity Check and Auto-Repair Plan

## Goal
To prevent launch failures due to missing client JARs or libraries by verifying their existence and integrity before launch, and automatically downloading missing files.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This feature will automatically potentially large files (client JARs ~30MB) if they are missing. This fits the user's request for "completing resources".

## Proposed Changes

### GeminiLauncher.Models
#### [MODIFY] [GameInstance.cs](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs)
- Add `ClientJarUrl` (string)
- Add `ClientJarSha1` (string)
- Add [FileSize](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs#732-738) (long)

### GeminiLauncher.Services
#### [MODIFY] [GameService.cs](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/GameService.cs)
- Update [ParseVersionJson](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/GameService.cs#46-138) to parse `downloads.client` object.
- Ensure `downloads.url` and `downloads.sha1` are captured.

#### [MODIFY] [LaunchService.cs](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs)
- Implement [ValidateAndRepairAsync](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs#228-283):
    - Check if `versions/{id}/{id}.jar` exists.
    - If missing:
        - Check if `ClientJarUrl` is available.
        - Trigger [DownloadService](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Network/DownloadService.cs#34-48) to download it.
        - Verify SHA1 (optional but recommended).
    - Iterate `game.Libraries`:
        - Check if file exists at `libraries/{path}`.
        - If missing:
             - Check `lib.Url`.
             - Download.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1.  Delete `1.19.1.jar` from the `.minecraft/versions/1.19.1` folder.
2.  Launch the game.
3.  Verify that the launcher shows "Repairing..." or "Downloading..." and successfully downloads the JAR.
4.  Game launches successfully.
